As you age, certain things stop being important to you, because your priorities change. 
That means that the #things you love right now might not mean much to you in a few years. 
According to Cosmopolitan, these things don't matter once you turn 25: 1. Wearing Makeup Every Single Day 
The older you are, the more comfortable you'll feel in your skin. 
That means you won't feel the need to constantly cover your face with makeup. 
You'll save it for the days you're going out.
